Created attachment 8985132
2windows_linkAffectsContent.gif

[Affected versions]:
- 60.0.1, 61.0b10, 62.0a1 (2018-06-12)

[Affected platforms]:
- Win 10x64;
- macOS 10.13.4;
- Ubuntu 16.04LTS

[Steps to reproduce]:
1. Launch Firefox;
2. Access about:preferences#privacy;
3. Scroll to Cookies and Site data section;
3. Open a new window(with either a normal/private tab);
4. Repeat step 2.

[Expected result]:
- In the first window nothing should change.

[Actual result]:
- The row with used site data is refreshed.

[Regression range]:
- last good: 2017-05-12
8a7d0b15595f9916123848ca906f29c62d4914c9
- first bad: 2017-05-13
96b36c5f527dd42e680a230839519eee1fc2c9f3

[Additional notes]:
- if no cookies/new data is stored that section should not refresh;
- attached screen-cast with the issue;
